15/08/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The ministry of labour and social policy reported on Thursday (14 August) that unemployment dropped to a four-year low of 13.2 per cent in July, down from 13.6 per cent in June. Sofia, with 3.76 per cent, had the lowest unemployment rate in the country, while the highest was in Turgovishte, where 29.3 per cent of the workforce is without jobs. According to the report, the economy created 17,465 jobs in July, and another 12,387 jobs were created under the government's special employment programmes. Private companies posted about 78 per cent of the new openings. (24 Chasa - 15/08/03; AP, BNT, bTV - 14/08/03)
